{"article_id":"09oK7P2sw2AOv8Yy","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The new Congress convenes on Tuesday ,","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"and almost immediately Republicans are going to get the ball rolling on repealing the Affordable Care Act","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"- eager to make headway","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"even before Donald Trump takes office .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"After more than 60 failed attempts","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"to curtail or repeal the 2010 law ,","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"Republican lawmakers have their opportunity","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"to make good on one of their top campaign promises .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"They seek to lessen government interference with people ' s health coverage choices","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"and relieve them of the punishing effects of mandates","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"to buy insurance .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"Democrats point to more than 20 million people","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"who have gained coverage through Obamacare","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"and argue","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"that mandates","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"to buy and offer insurance","depth":12},{"id":16,"text":"are necessary","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"to support a market","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"that includes high-risk individuals .","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"But the law ' s individual insurance markets in many parts of the country are radically shrinking ,","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"even while premiums steeply rise .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"That has left many people with fewer , more costly choices .","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"\" Given the dire situation","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"facing our country ,","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"the time","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"to act","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"is now","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"to deliver immediate relief for the American people , \"","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"said House Speaker Paul Ryan","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"( R )","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"of Wisconsin just before Christmas .","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"From Republicans ' first attempt","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"to beat back the law","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"until now , however , the overriding question has been :","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"What would a GOP replacement look like ?","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"They haven ' t been able to agree on one .","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"Not only is it still unclear what Republicans might rally around ,","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"a big question is over timing","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"- whether Republicans are making a mistake","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"by going quickly for repeal","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"without first outlining what a replacement would look like .","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"\" In some ways , I feel","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"we ' re putting the cart before the horse , \"","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"says Sen. Susan Collins , the Republican moderate from Maine .","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"She wants a detailed replacement framework","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"to accompany the repeal push .","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"That could prevent uncertainty over a final outcome from disrupting insurance markets and service .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"Maine has 84,000 residents","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"who are covered by the law .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"The repeal legislation is expected to name some future date","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"at which many key parts of Obamacare will end ,","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"allowing an interim period","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"for participants to stay covered","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"while a replacement is drafted .","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"Republicans disagree on when that date should be - perhaps three years hence ,","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"to allow plenty of time","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"to draft a replacement , or sooner ,","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"before this Congress ends in two years","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"and the GOP potentially loses its grip in midterm elections .","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"And","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"while House Republicans have drafted a blueprint for replacement under their \" A Better Way \" agenda ,","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"Senate Republicans have yet to coalesce around any replacement plan .","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"So it ' s not at all clear that Republicans in both chambers will be able to agree on a replacement in the given time frame ,","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"let alone get buy-in from Democrats .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"Republicans can repeal with only a majority vote through a special budget process ,","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"but legislation","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"to replace the law","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"would have to clear a 60-vote threshold in the Senate ,","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"where Republicans hold a narrow 52-to-48 advantage .","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"That ' s why Senator Collins thinks","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"lawmakers need to see a detailed path forward upfront .","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"\" I don ' t want people falling through the cracks","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"and losing their insurance status","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"because we didn ' t have a replacement","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"ready to go , \"","depth":14},{"id":75,"text":"she said in an interview ,","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"noting from her experience","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"overseeing insurance for Maine","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"that insurance markets \" are complex","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"and that they can not turn on a dime . \"","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"Her concern is backed up by a recent report by the center-left Brookings Institution think tank in Washington .","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"A repeal effort \" would likely destabilize the individual market","depth":14},{"id":82,"text":"and very possibly cause it to collapse in some regions of the country during the interim period","depth":15},{"id":83,"text":"before any replacement is designed , \"","depth":15},{"id":84,"text":"the Brookings report found .","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"\" If you ' ve said","depth":16},{"id":86,"text":"' this whole structure is gone , '","depth":16},{"id":87,"text":"even if you set a date a year later or six months later ,","depth":15},{"id":88,"text":"insurance companies are promptly going to begin making decisions ,","depth":15},{"id":89,"text":"they ' re going to change what they offer , where and at what prices , \"","depth":15},{"id":90,"text":"said Sen. Chris Coons","depth":15},{"id":91,"text":"( D )","depth":15},{"id":92,"text":"of Delaware just before the holiday break .","depth":14},{"id":93,"text":"\" I think","depth":13},{"id":94,"text":"it ' s going to lead to chaos .","depth":13},{"id":95,"text":"\" Of course it would be preferable to have worked out a game plan , and particularly a bipartisan one , before a repeal vote ,","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"says G. William Hoagland , senior vice president at the Bipartisan Policy Center in Washington .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"But he says","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"there ' s a great concern among Republicans of time wasted and perhaps an opportunity","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"lost","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"to repeal Obamacare at all","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"if they wait to get everyone","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"- including some Democrats -","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"on board with a replacement plan .","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"One way","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"to seize the day","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"without triggering serious instability in the insurance market","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"would be to provide in the repeal legislation a fund","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"to help insurers weather the interim period ,","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"Mr. Hoagland says .","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"\" I think","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"what the insurers will want to know is not so much the end product , or replacement ,","depth":13},{"id":112,"text":"but what will you do for the transition period","depth":14},{"id":113,"text":"to lessen volatility , \"","depth":14},{"id":114,"text":"he says .","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"That appears to align with a comment","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"provided to the Monitor by David Merritt , executive vice president of America ' s Health Insurance Plans , the heath insurance trade association .","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"`` While political realities will likely lead to a repeal vote","depth":14},{"id":118,"text":"before an effective replacement plan is outlined ,","depth":14},{"id":119,"text":"consumers will be best served by an effective transition","depth":14},{"id":120,"text":"that delivers continuous coverage , \"","depth":14},{"id":121,"text":"Mr. Merritt wrote in an email .","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"The House committee","depth":5},{"id":123,"text":"that ' s working on the repeal legislation","depth":5},{"id":124,"text":"promises more details soon .","depth":4},{"id":125,"text":"Broadly , Americans can expect to see a two-step process","depth":6},{"id":126,"text":"known as \" budget reconciliation \"","depth":6},{"id":127,"text":"that will allow Republicans to repeal key parts of Obamacare with just a simple majority vote in both houses .","depth":5},{"id":128,"text":"The Senate is expected to take the first step in a vote","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"- likely this week -","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"that sets up the process .","depth":7},{"id":131,"text":"House Republicans are expected to follow suit on Jan. 9 .","depth":7},{"id":132,"text":"This stage is expected to go easily .","depth":7},{"id":133,"text":"It ' s the second step ,","depth":8},{"id":134,"text":"where the actual repeal vote takes place ,","depth":8},{"id":135,"text":"where things could get dicey .","depth":7},{"id":136,"text":"The GOP might lack the votes","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"they need in the Senate ,","depth":8},{"id":138,"text":"Hoagland says .","depth":7},{"id":139,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":6},{"id":140,"text":"you care about","depth":6},{"id":141,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":5},{"id":142,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":5},{"id":143,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":5},{"id":144,"text":"Collins might balk at undoing coverage for 20 million Americans ,","depth":8},{"id":145,"text":"even if the effect is delayed ,","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"with no replacement in sight .","depth":7},{"id":147,"text":"A couple senators on the right might think","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"the repeal legislation does n't go far enough ,","depth":8},{"id":149,"text":"Hoagland adds .","depth":7},{"id":150,"text":"It would take only three Republican defections to kill the repeal vote","depth":6},{"id":151,"text":"if all Democrats stuck together in opposition .","depth":6},{"id":152,"text":"In the meantime , Democrats want to turn up the heat on Republicans","depth":5},{"id":153,"text":"so that voting for repeal becomes too politically uncomfortable for some .","depth":5},{"id":154,"text":"President Obama will head to the Hill on Wednesday","depth":5},{"id":155,"text":"and meet with Democrats","depth":5},{"id":156,"text":"to discuss how to defend his healthcare legacy .","depth":4},{"id":157,"text":"It ' s not clear whether they ' ll succeed .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":315,"left":296,"right":314,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":296,"left":279,"right":295,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":279,"left":161,"right":278,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":161,"left":0,"right":160,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":160,"left":1,"right":159,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":159,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"context","nuclearity"